Transcription.Text: Mr. Luthuli cannot speak freely to us. But he must draw encouragement from the re- ception that he will receive here and elsewhere on his journey. "Who will deny", he has said sadly, "that thirty years of my life have been spent in knocking in vain at a closed and barred door?
